# Git Commit Message Template for ESP32 Fish Tank Automation

# Use this template for commit messages to maintain consistency
# Syntax: git commit -m "vX.Y.Z: [type] Description"

# ============================================================================
# VERSION BUMP COMMIT MESSAGE FORMAT
# ============================================================================

# v3.0.1: [patch] Add OLED display rotation support
# 
# - Added display.setRotation(1) for 90° clockwise rotation
# - Updated version to 3.0.1
# - Updated CHANGELOG.md and README.md
# - No breaking changes

# ============================================================================
# EXAMPLES
# ============================================================================

# For Patch Updates (Z bump):
# v3.0.1: [patch] Add OLED display rotation
# v3.0.2: [patch] Fix temperature sensor recovery logic
# v3.0.3: [patch] Optimize memory usage for OLED display

# For Minor Updates (Y bump):
# v3.1.0: [minor] Add web dashboard interface
# v3.2.0: [minor] Add new WiFi auto-reconnect feature
# v3.3.0: [minor] Add data logging capability

# For Major Updates (X bump):
# v4.0.0: [major] Support multi-tank networked control
# v5.0.0: [major] Redesign REST API with v2 endpoints

# ============================================================================
# COMMIT MESSAGE STRUCTURE
# ============================================================================

# Line 1: vX.Y.Z: [type] Short description (50 chars max)
# Line 2: (blank)
# Line 3+: Detailed explanation (72 chars per line)
#         - What changed
#         - Why it changed
#         - Impact or notes

# ============================================================================
# TYPES
# ============================================================================

# [patch]  - Z bump - Bug fixes, small improvements, tweaks
# [minor]  - Y bump - New features, non-breaking additions
# [major]  - X bump - Breaking changes, significant redesigns
# [docs]   - Documentation only (no version bump usually)
# [ci]     - CI/CD configuration (no version bump)

# ============================================================================
# FULL EXAMPLE
# ============================================================================

# v3.0.1: [patch] Add OLED display rotation support
#
# Added display.setRotation(1) to support rotated hardware configurations.
# This allows the OLED display to work correctly when the hardware is
# positioned upside-down or at different angles.
#
# - Added setRotation(1) after OLED initialization
# - Supports 4 rotation levels: 0°, 90°, 180°, 270°
# - Backward compatible with existing deployments
# - Updated documentation with rotation options
#
# Files changed:
# - esp32-scheduler.ino
# - README.md
# - CHANGELOG.md
# - VERSION.md
#
# Testing:
# - Compiled successfully
# - Display rotation verified on hardware
# - All other functions working normally

